==English==

===Etymology===
From the name of the Italian statesman and writer Niccolò ''Machiavekki'' (1469-1527), whose work ''The Prince'' (1532) advises that [[acquiring ]] and [[exercising]] power may require [[unethical]] methods.

===Adjective===
'''Machiavellian'''
# [[Cunning]], [[scheming]], and [[unscrupulous]].

====Translations====
*Finnish: [[machiavelliläinen]]

